[{"location":"ensembles/#Ensemble","page":"Ensemble","title":"Ensemble","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"ensembles/","page":"Ensemble","title":"Ensemble","text":"The Ensemble type provides a structured container for managing ensembles of model simulations. Each ensemble may consist of input parameters, output variables, styling metadata, model objects, and optional ensemble weights.","category":"page"},{"location":"ensembles/#Type-Definition","page":"Ensemble","title":"Type Definition","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"ensembles/","page":"Ensemble","title":"Ensemble","text":"mutable struct Ensemble <: AbstractEnsemble\n    N::Integer\n    path::Vector{String}\n    mpath::Vector{String}\n    set::Vector{Integer}\n    p::DataFrames.DataFrame\n    s::DataFrames.DataFrame\n    w::Union{Array,AbstractEnsembleWeights}\n    v::Dict{Union{String,Symbol},Any}\n    m::Vector{AbstractModel}\nend","category":"page"},{"location":"ensembles/","page":"Ensemble","title":"Ensemble","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"ensembles/#Creating-an-Ensemble","page":"Ensemble","title":"Creating an Ensemble","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"ensembles/#Manual-Construction","page":"Ensemble","title":"Manual Construction","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"ensembles/","page":"Ensemble","title":"Ensemble","text":"To construct an ensemble manually:","category":"page"},{"location":"ensembles/","page":"Ensemble","title":"Ensemble","text":"ens = Ensemble()\n\n# Populate fields\nens.N = 10\nens.path = [\"./ensemble1\"]\nens.mpath = [\"./ensemble1/member1\", \"./ensemble1/member2\", ...]\nens.set = fill(1, ens.N)\nens.p = DataFrame(param1 = rand(ens.N), param2 = rand(ens.N))\nens.s = DataFrame(color = [\"red\", \"blue\", ...])\nens.v[:temperature] = [temp1, temp2, ...]  # YAXArrays\nens.m = [model1, model2, ...]              # AbstractModel instances","category":"page"},{"location":"ensembles/","page":"Ensemble","title":"Ensemble","text":"This method gives you full control and is suitable for dynamically generated ensembles.","category":"page"},{"location":"ensembles/","page":"Ensemble","title":"Ensemble","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"ensembles/#From-Directory-Path","page":"Ensemble","title":"From Directory Path","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"ensembles/","page":"Ensemble","title":"Ensemble","text":"You can also load ensembles automatically using a directory path or a list of paths:","category":"page"},{"location":"ensembles/","page":"Ensemble","title":"Ensemble","text":"ens = Ensemble(\"path/to/ensemble1\")\nens = Ensemble([\"path/to/ens2a\", \"path/to/ens2b\"])","category":"page"},{"location":"ensembles/#Optional-Keyword-Arguments","page":"Ensemble","title":"Optional Keyword Arguments","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"ensembles/","page":"Ensemble","title":"Ensemble","text":"sort_by::String: Sort members using a column from the parameter DataFrame.","category":"page"},{"location":"ensembles/","page":"Ensemble","title":"Ensemble","text":"These constructors initialize the following fields:","category":"page"},{"location":"ensembles/","page":"Ensemble","title":"Ensemble","text":"N, path, mpath, set, p, s","category":"page"},{"location":"ensembles/","page":"Ensemble","title":"Ensemble","text":"Remaining fields (w, v, m) can be filled in later.","category":"page"},{"location":"ensembles/","page":"Ensemble","title":"Ensemble","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"ensembles/#Saving-an-Ensemble","page":"Ensemble","title":"Saving an Ensemble","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"ensembles/","page":"Ensemble","title":"Ensemble","text":"To save an ensemble to a JLD2 file:","category":"page"},{"location":"ensembles/","page":"Ensemble","title":"Ensemble","text":"ensemble_save(\"output_file.jld2\", ens, \"ens\")","category":"page"},{"location":"ensembles/","page":"Ensemble","title":"Ensemble","text":"output_file.jld2: Target file name.\nens: The ensemble to be saved.\n\"ens\": Key under which to store the ensemble in the file.","category":"page"},{"location":"ensembles/","page":"Ensemble","title":"Ensemble","text":"Uses JLD2.jldopen internally.","category":"page"},{"location":"ensembles/","page":"Ensemble","title":"Ensemble","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"ensembles/#Example-Workflow","page":"Ensemble","title":"Example Workflow","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"ensembles/","page":"Ensemble","title":"Ensemble","text":"# Load ensemble from path\nens = Ensemble(\"runs/experiment1\")\n\n# Add variables and models\nens.v[:smb] = load_smb_outputs(ens.mpath)\nens.m = [load_model(mpath) for mpath in ens.mpath]\n\n# Save to file\nensemble_save(\"output/ensemble_exp1.jld2\", ens, \"ens\")","category":"page"},{"location":"ensembles/","page":"Ensemble","title":"Ensemble","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"ensembles/#Notes","page":"Ensemble","title":"Notes","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"ensembles/","page":"Ensemble","title":"Ensemble","text":"Variables (v) are expected to be YAXArrays or collections thereof.\nWeights (w) may be an array or a custom AbstractEnsembleWeights.\nThe type AbstractModel must be defined elsewhere in your codebase to suit your model structure.","category":"page"},{"location":"ensembles/","page":"Ensemble","title":"Ensemble","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"#ModelAnalysis.jl-Documentation","page":"ModelAnalysis.jl Documentation","title":"ModelAnalysis.jl Documentation","text":"","category":"section"}]
